  "prompt": "I got placed in TCS's EIS stream in my campus placement. Will I get a job in EIS or in IT?",
  "response": "Congratulations on your placement with TCS! The EIS stream, which stands for Engineering and Industrial Services, is a specific division within TCS that focuses on providing engineering and technology services to clients in various industries. This stream is distinct from the more general IT services division.\n\nAs you've been placed in the EIS stream, it's likely that your initial role will be related to engineering and industrial services rather than the broader IT services. However, roles and projects within TCS can vary and may overlap with IT-related work, depending on the specific needs of the clients and the projects you're assigned to.\n\nIt's also possible that over time, you might have opportunities to move between streams or work on projects that align with your interests and career goals. If you have specific preferences or aspirations, it's a good idea to discuss them with your HR representative or during your onboarding process to understand how TCS can accommodate your career development.",
